This paper deals with generalized additive models (GAMs) in the multiclass setting, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning and statistical modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also discusses interpretability of GAMs, which could potentially fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
